						               													<description>Minikin Saga: Jewels is a competitive micro game for 2 to 3 players. Where players as thieves stole a gem from a masquerade and must escape undetected, by revealing the opponents' identities and use them as scapegoat before they discover theirs.&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game, players will draw 2 Pawns from a bag, the combinations of those pawn's colors will determine is your identity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn you must do 1 Action from the 3 possible:&amp;#10;-Interrogate: Move a card (You can flip it too) to another empty space and ask a question. This question must refer to what the opponent's character can see. ex. Your Suspect see a Bird? Your Suspect can't see the color, Yellow? This is going to give you information about their identity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-Investigate: At random and without looking inside the bag, take a pawn and look at it in secret. This will reveal what color is not in play and its not part of someone&amp;rsquo;s identity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-Accuse: Point to an opponent (The other player closes their eyes in a 3 Player Game) and point to a card, if you discover the opponent's identity you win the game (In a 3 Player Game you must discover the other player's identity too) If not you lose that action and you must reveal one of your pawns to the accused player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when a player discovers all the opponents' identities, that player is the winner!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
